WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Squax' is a Workbench game where the goal is to move large
square shaped tiles so they match various patterns, in the least
amount of moves possible.

  You play the game by clicking on any large square tile that is
surrounded by 8 other tiles, empty spaces or smaller square tiles.
Each surrounding tile of the same size will 'rotate' by 90 degrees
clockwise around the clicked tile, as the following example shows:

 a.b       ..a       .c.
 .*.   ->  c*.   ->  .*.  etc.
 .c.       ..b       b.a

  ...where the letters 'a', 'b' and 'c' are the tiles, the '*' is
the clicked tile and the dots ('.') are the empty spaces.

  To help you in matching patterns, smaller square tiles indicate
where you have to put the larger tiles. You can also click on a
'Figure' button, which will briefly show the pattern to match.

  Have fun!

